The Egyptian rousette (

 Rousettus aegyptiacus

) is publicly classified as the Marburg virus-host and has a wide geographical distribution. The pretended cause for the dispersal of MVD might be the close contact between humans and animals like, other than human primates, bats, and cattle (Towner et al.     ). It has been listed by World Health Organization (WHO) as a category 4 risk agent because of its lethality (Chosewood and Wilson     ).
